The cipher belongs to the group of so-called single-alphabetical wildcard cipher
When using the ciphers of this group, each character of the plaintext is replace
by a certain character fixed in this key of the same alphabet.
Key selection methods may vary. The key in Caesar's cipher is an arbitrary numbe
selected in the range from one to twenty-five. Each letter of the plaintext is r
